We have been developing a biped robot based on the passive nature of dynamics~\cite{Sakurai2024-rt}.
In this study, to elucidate how the passive dynamics of the musculoskeletal robot contribute to learning, we proposed a simplified robot model (Fig.~\ref{fig:robot}).
Specifically, this model was developed by extracting only the lower body from a previously developed musculoskeletal robot using the dynamics simulator MuJoCo.
The leg length and body mass are $0.78$~[m] and $6.38$~[kg], respectively. The detailed length, mass, and inertial parameters are shown in Table~\ref{table:passive_model_mass}.
