\label{sec:results}
\subsection{Does RL Expand Agent Capability?}
We begin with the central question. Table~\ref{tab:capability} reports the capability boundary of each model at full evaluation budget ($k = 64$, $T = 5$), measured as the set of problems each model can solve at least once. The critical column is $|\mathcal{B}_{\text{RL}} \setminus \mathcal{B}_{\text{base}}|$: problems that the RL agent can solve but the base agent cannot solve in any of 64 attempts with 5 search rounds.
