Table~\ref{tab:saturation_full} reports interaction saturation points $T^\star$ at multiple $\epsilon$ thresholds, using $k_{\max} = 64$. The main-text number ($\epsilon = 0.02$) is stable to perturbations of $\epsilon \in [0.01, 0.05]$: $\pirl$ never saturates later than $\pisft$ on Category C, but the plateau height is always higher.
