\section{Introduction}
Reinforcement Learning (RL) has been proven to be a catalyst for eliciting the reasoning capabilities of Large Language Models (LLMs)~\citep{guo2025deepseek,team2025kimi,hui2025decif}. This capability is particularly pivotal in long-context scenarios. Real-world long-context tasks, such as long-dialogue history understanding and long structured data analysis, are characterized not only by their extensive input lengths but also by the necessity for deep comprehension and complex reasoning over the content. In addition, enhancing long-context understanding is instrumental for LLM agents in managing extended trajectories.
